@startuml CI/CD Pipeline

title Deployment View — CI/CD (GitHub Actions → GHCR)

actor "Developer" as dev
participant "GitHub\n(main branch / tag)" as github
participant "GitHub Actions" as ci
participant "GitHub Container\nRegistry (GHCR)" as ghcr

== Quality Gate (every push to main / PR) ==

dev -> github: Push commit or open PR
github -> ci: Trigger workflow
ci -> ci: Backend: dotnet build + dotnet test\n(Testcontainers, PostgreSQL)
ci -> ci: Frontend: npx playwright test\n(full Docker Compose stack)
ci -> ci: Docs: asciidoctor build\n(arc42 → HTML5)
ci -> github: Deploy docs to GitHub Pages

== Image Publishing (version tag push) ==

dev -> github: Push tag (e.g. frontend/v1.0.0)
github -> ci: Trigger release workflow
ci -> ci: Build Docker image for tagged component
ci -> ghcr: Push image\nghcr.io/maik-hasler/einsatzbereit/<component>:v1.0.0

note over ci,ghcr
  Each component is versioned independently.
  Tags: frontend/v*, backend/v*, keycloak/v*
  See VERSIONING.md for the full strategy.
end note

@enduml
